ust me, and that pencil.{&1310}\par And nothing happened.{&1310}\par Seconds passed.{&1310}\par Minutes passed.{&1310}\par ... and nothing happened.{&1310}\par "No! Like you did it before!" Tess abruptly screeched at me, breaking my concentration. My eyes floundered over at her.{&1310}\par "Wh-what? I don't even - I don't know \i what \i0 I did ..."{&1310}\par Tess's head collapsed down against my thigh, and I heard her exasperated sigh. I blinked, but she bounced back to her feet, shaking her head quickly away.{&1310}\par "That's okay. That's okay," she was hugging me around the neck from behind. "You did it. You \i finally\i0  did it. That's what matters. I saw it. I \i saw\i0  it, Ev."{&1310}\par I wasn't sure what to say or think. I don't know that it mattered as much that I couldn't do it again just yet. I had done it once, and I could do it again. I wasn't mundane. All those kids in class. Halloway. \i Everyone\i0 . They were all wrong.{&1310}\par They were all ... wrong.{&1310}\par I got excited. Then it almost just as quickly deflated with a sudden rush of despairing air.{&1310}\par "No one will believe me," I groaned in sudden realization, and Tess almost slapped me.{&1310}\par "They won't believe you either!" I growled back. She shook her head.{&1310}\par "Who cares?" Her hands came up emphatically. "You did it once - you can do it again! At least you know you \i can\i0  ..."{&1310}\par Maybe. Maybe she was right. But I didn't know how-{&1310}\par The front door opened. I heard it slam back on its hinges, and jumped in my seat.{&1310}\par Tess and I both spun around toward my bedroom door ...{&1310}\par Just in time to see dad come storming in.\cf2 {&1310}\par }{&1310}
